sequenceDiagram
    participant Kernel as Linux Kernel 5.4.210 (ARM32)
    participant BPF as BPF Program (stb_connect.bpf.o)
    participant Maps as BPF Maps (perf_map, connect_start)
    participant Userspace as Userspace Probe (stb_ebpf_probe)
    participant PerfBuf as Perf Buffer (perf_event_array)
    participant Serializer as Serializer (JSON)
    participant TCP as TCP Client
    participant Relay as Relay Server (192.168.58.130:9104)
    participant Backend as Backend (data-ingest → ClickHouse)

    Note over Kernel,Backend: === 启动初始化流程 ===

    Userspace->>Userspace: main() → setup_signal_handlers()
    Userspace->>Userspace: loader_init() → set_legacy_mode()
    activate Userspace
    Userspace->>BPF: loader_load("stb_connect.bpf.o")
    activate BPF
    BPF->>BPF: bpf_object__open_file() (no BTF)
    BPF->>BPF: bpf_object__load() → load to kernel
    BPF->>Maps: bpf_map__fd(perf_map)
    BPF->>Maps: bpf_map__fd(connect_start)
    deactivate BPF
    deactivate Userspace

    Userspace->>BPF: loader_attach()
    activate Userspace
    activate BPF
    BPF->>Kernel: bpf_program__attach_tracepoint("syscalls", "sys_enter_connect")
    Kernel-->>BPF: link_enter (success)
    BPF->>Kernel: bpf_program__attach_tracepoint("syscalls", "sys_exit_connect")
    Kernel-->>BPF: link_exit (success)
    deactivate BPF
    deactivate Userspace

    Userspace->>Userspace: perf_monitor_init(perf_map_fd, ring_buf)
    Userspace->>Userspace: serializer_init(MAX_EVENTS_PER_BATCH, BATCH_FLUSH_TIMEOUT_MS)
    Userspace->>Userspace: tcp_client_init(RELAY_SERVER_IP, RELAY_SERVER_PORT)
    Userspace->>TCP: tcp_client_connect()
    activate TCP
    TCP->>Relay: TCP connect 192.168.58.130:9104
    Relay-->>TCP: Connected
    deactivate TCP

    Note over Kernel,Backend: === 事件采集流程 (sys_enter_connect) ===

    Kernel->>BPF: tracepoint (sys_enter_connect)
    activate Kernel
    activate BPF
    BPF->>BPF: get_pid_tgid() → pid, tid
    BPF->>BPF: bpf_probe_read_user(args → fd, user_addr, addr_len)
    BPF->>BPF: read_sockaddr_in() → family, daddr, dport
    BPF->>Maps: bpf_map_update_elem(connect_start, pid_tgid, timestamp_ns)
    BPF->>BPF: Fill connect_event_t (enter)
    BPF->>Maps: bpf_perf_event_output(ctx, perf_map, BPF_F_CURRENT_CPU, event)
    Note right of BPF: Event sent to perf buffer
    deactivate BPF
    deactivate Kernel

    Note over Kernel,Backend: === 事件采集流程 (sys_exit_connect) ===

    Kernel->>BPF: tracepoint (sys_exit_connect)
    activate Kernel
    activate BPF
    BPF->>Maps: bpf_map_lookup_elem(connect_start, pid_tgid)
    Maps-->>BPF: start_timestamp_ns
    BPF->>BPF: Calculate latency_us = (now - start) / 1000
    BPF->>Maps: bpf_map_delete_elem(connect_start, pid_tgid)
    BPF->>BPF: Fill connect_event_t (exit)
    BPF->>Maps: bpf_perf_event_output(ctx, perf_map, BPF_F_CURRENT_CPU, event)
    Note right of BPF: Event sent to perf buffer
    deactivate BPF
    deactivate Kernel

    Note over Kernel,Backend: === 用户态主循环 (每 100ms) ===

    loop while (!g_stop_requested)
        Userspace->>PerfBuf: perf_monitor_poll_once(monitor, 100)
        activate Userspace
        activate PerfBuf
        PerfBuf->>PerfBuf: perf_buffer__poll(pb, 100ms)
        Note over PerfBuf: Kernel delivers events via perf buffer
        PerfBuf->>Userspace: event_handler(ctx, cpu, data, size)
        activate Userspace
        Userspace->>Userspace: ring_buffer_push(ring_buf, event)
        deactivate Userspace
        deactivate PerfBuf

        Userspace->>Userspace: ring_buffer_pop(ring_buf, &event)
        Note over Userspace: Phase 2: Read events from ring buffer
        
        Userspace->>Serializer: serializer_add_event(serializer, &event)
        activate Serializer
        Serializer->>Serializer: Add to batch buffer
        deactivate Serializer

        alt Batch full or timeout
            Userspace->>Serializer: serializer_flush(serializer, json_buf, size)
            activate Serializer
            Serializer->>Serializer: connect_event_t → JSON
            Note over Serializer: {"probe_id":"stb-tyson-01", "timestamp":"...", "events":[...]}
            Serializer-->>Userspace: json_buf (serialized)
            deactivate Serializer

            Userspace->>TCP: tcp_client_send_line(tcp_client, json_buf)
            activate TCP
            TCP->>Relay: send(json_line + "\n")
            activate Relay
            Relay->>Backened: Forward JSON to data-ingest :9104
            activate Backened
            Backened->>Backened: Parse JSON → INSERT INTO cloudflow.ebpf_events
            deactivate Backened
            Relay-->>TCP: ACK
            deactivate Relay
            deactivate TCP
        end
    end

    Note over Kernel,Backend: === 信号处理 + 清理 ===

    Kernel->>Userspace: Signal (SIGINT / SIGTERM)
    activate Kernel
    Userspace->>Userspace: signal_handler() → g_stop_requested = 1
    deactivate Kernel

    Userspace->>Userspace: cleanup_all()
    Userspace->>TCP: tcp_client_cleanup() → close socket
    Userspace->>Serializer: serializer_cleanup()
    Userspace->>PerfBuf: perf_monitor_stop() → perf_buffer__free()
    Userspace->>BPF: loader_unload() → detach + unload BPF
    Userspace->>Userspace: print_runtime_stats()
    Note over Userspace: Total events, sent, dropped, CPU, memory
